<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Bible Questions | Scoreboard</title>
    <base href="/">

    <!-- Styles -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles/global.css">

    <!-- Local Scripts -->
    <script src="scripts/global.js" defer></script>
</head>

<body>
    <%- include('partials/header') %>
        <main>
            <h2>Hi There!!!</h2>
            <p>This demo utilizies Netlify for static site hosting, an Express app that runs using Netlify's functions,
                and EJS for templating. This is currently my starter code for projects that I want to develop quickly.
            </p>
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <p>To use this site, you'll need a Netlify account (<a href="https://app.netlify.com/signup" target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer">sign up here</a>).</p>
            <p>You can link your site to a GitHub repo following this <a
                    href="https://docs.netlify.com/get-started/#deploy-a-project-to-netlify" target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer">guide</a>, and using the following settings:</p>
            <ul class="build-settings">
                <li>Base directory: <code>/</code></li>
                <li>Build command: <code>npm install && npm run build</code></li>
                <li>Publish directory: <code>src/</code></li>
                <li>Functions directory: <code>netlify/functions</code></li>
            </ul>
            <p>Finally, you'll need to setup the Netlify CLI to develop locally (<a
                    href="https://docs.netlify.com/cli/get-started/" target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer">instructions</a>).</p>
            <h2>Random Route</h2>
            <form action="javascript:void(0)">
                <label>Type something random!&nbsp;<input maxlength="17" value="<%= locals.string || '' %>"></label>
            </form>
            <% if (locals.string) { %>
                <div class="output">
                    <style>
                        span::before,span::after {
                            content: "<%= string %>";
                        }
                    </style>
                    <span><%= string %></span>
                </div>
            <% } %>
        </main>
        <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>

</html>